.json` resources | explicit direct API/Kit/package resolution |\n34: \n35: ## Instructions\n36: \n37: - If any entry is unresolved, run a capability resolution session before phase implementation.\n38: - Capability resolution may update only platform-capability-check.json/md.\n39: - A real HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package must be used when available; do not close with local mock, in-memory data, sample data, or generic fallback.\n40: - Use resolved-deferred only after checking CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, SDK declarations, and package lookup when relevant.\n41: - Use capability-sdk-probe-cache.json as preparation evidence for SDK declaration/library candidates; it is not authority by itself.\n42: - Treat ArkTS/native/overview declarations as discovery-only until a Cangjie-callable API, wrapper, FFI, bridge, or compile probe is recorded.\n43: - When compileProbeRecommended is true, run a bounded target-context compile probe or record the concrete SDK/tooling blocker before phase implementation.\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Platform Capability Pre-Resolution\n\n- Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n\n## Purpose\n\nPhase-scoped platform capability pre-resolution checklist. This is generated from phase-task-checklist.json and platform-capability-check.json before phase implementation. All current-phase critical/high platform capabilities must be resolved before target code edits begin.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phasePlatformCapabilities | 1 |\n| unresolvedPlatformCapabilities | 0 |\n| compileProbeRecommendedCapabilities | 0 |\n| discoveryOnlyCapabilities | 0 |\n| sdkProbeDeclarationCandidateCapabilities | 1 |\n\n## Resolution Status Counts\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-capability-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782529601586,"end":1782529601596}},"id":"prt_f070b30020013qQJ4hLCRa9jAq","sessionID":"ses_0f8f